      • getType

        public static BiomeDictionary.Type getType(java.lang.String name,
                           BiomeDictionary.Type... subTypes)
        Retrieves a Type value by name, if one does not exist already it creates one. This can be used as interm measure for modders to add there own category of Biome. There are NO naming conventions besides: MUST be all upper case (enforced by name.toUpper()) NO Special characters. {Unenforced, just don't be a pain, if it becomes a issue I WILL make this RTE with no worry about backwards compatibility} Note: For performance sake, the return value of this function SHOULD be cached. Two calls with the same name SHOULD return the same value.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of this Type
        Returns:
        An instance of Type for this name.
